kw.arg:
DescriptionEdit=Analyze the document, if the bold, uppercase and underlined text which is present in the middle of the first page of the document matches with any one of the following key words given below then classify it into 'Pleadings'.
1.Motion to Amend 2.Motion to Compel 3.Motion to Strike 4.Motion for Protective Order 5.Motion to Dismiss 6.Motion for Sanctions 7.Motion to Enforce 8.Notice of Compliance 9.Motion of Continuance 10.Notice of Readiness of Trials 11.Notice of Unavailability 12.Exhibit List 13.Witness List 14.Expert Witness List 15.Motion in Limine 16.Verdict Form 17.Jury Instructions 18.Motion to Abid 19.Fact Witness List 20.Motion for Entry of Final Judgment 21.Motion for Summary Judgment 22.Motion for Summary Disposition 23.Motion for Judgment on Pleadings 24.Motion for 57.105 25.Motion for Extension of Time on Plaintiff's Fact Sheet (PFS) 26.Motion for Extension of Time to Respond to Discovery 27.Motion to Compel Deposition 28.Notice of Withdrawal 29.Motion for Relief from Technical Admissions 30.Motion to Appear Virtually 31.Motion to Transfer Venue 32.Disclosure of Fee Expert 33.Stipulation of Entitlement to Attorney's Fees and Costs 34.Joint Motion to Excuse Client's Appearance 35.Joint Stipulation Appointing Mediator 36.Motion to Vacate Default 37.Notice of Appel 38.Appellant's Initial Brief 39.Reply Brief 40.Appellee's Answer Brief 41.Notice of Filing 42.Record on Appeal 43.Notice of Appearance as Co-Counsel 44.Acknowledgement of New Case (Appeals) 45.Joint Stipulation to Conduct Mediation 46.Notice of Hearing Do not classify any letter which belongs to correspondence into 'Pleadings'.
Any Notice or Motion should be classified under 'Pleadings' except any document that has 'Motion to Depositions ' in it .
